summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling previous resolutions on Lebanon, particularly 425 (1978) and 426 (1978), 
Recalling the Secretary-General's conclusion that Israel had withdrawn its forces from Lebanon in accordance with resolution 425 (1978),

1. Endorses the report of the Secretary-General on UNIFIL and renews its mandate for six months; 
2. Decides to extend the present mandate until 31 July 2003; 
3. Takes note of UNIFIL's reconfiguration; 
4. Reiterates support for Lebanon's territorial integrity, sovereignty, and political independence; 
5. Commends Lebanon for steps to ensure its authority in the south and calls for continued measures; 
6. Calls on parties to ensure UNIFIL's freedom of movement; 
7. Reiterates the call on parties to respect the withdrawal line and cooperate with UNIFIL; 
8. Condemns acts of violence and urges parties to respect UNIFIL's safety; 
9. Supports UNIFIL's efforts to maintain the ceasefire; 
10. Welcomes UNIFIL's contribution to demining and encourages further assistance; 
11. Requests the Secretary-General to continue consultations and report to the Council; 
12. Looks forward to the early fulfilment of UNIFIL's mandate; 
13. Stresses the need for a comprehensive, just, and lasting peace in the Middle East.
